st improvements. First, there is no reason to believe that we&#8217;ll stop=
 installing more solar panels, and in doing so, the cost of solar panels wi=
ll continue to decline. Second, technological improvements like thinner or =
more efficient panels should continue to drive down costs. And finally, the=
 whole ecosystem around solar should become more efficient &#8212; everythi=
ng from the cost of capital to permitting costs &#8212; as solar becomes mo=
re ubiquitous and an even more important component of our energy mix.</p><p=
 style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">Let&#8217;s keep driving down that curve until we have sola=
r energy too cheap to meter.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-si=
